-- src.http --
< {%
This stuff here is a script, I know it doesn't look like it
but that's because the lexer doesn't actually care what's in
between the open and close token.

It can literally be anything, including random paragraphs like this.

Look, here's an ASCII egg:

       _____
     ,'     `.
    /         \
   |           |
   |           |
    \         /
     `._____,'

Come to think of it, I think I want some way of supporting more than
just JS script blocks, perhaps a markdown codeblock style indicating
what language it is, defaulting to JS for compatibility with other tools
as that's what they do.

Anyway this has been long enough, let's close the script.
%}
